                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-221-off1279 t18200412-221-victim2081"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-221-person2082">
                  GEORGE 
                  RICHARDSON
               <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2082" type="surname" value="RICHARDSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2082" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2082" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t18200412-221-crimeloc1281">Upper East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-221-crimeloc1281" type="placeName" value="Upper East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-221-crimeloc1281" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-221-off1279 t18200412-221-crimeloc1281"></join>, and am an <rs id="t18200412-221-viclabel1282" type="occupation">optician</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-221-victim2081 t18200412-221-viclabel1282"></join> - the telescope was in the window. The window had been broken before, and having been frequently robbed, I attached it by a piece of wire to a bell. I stopped the hole that had been made in the window by a compass box, and had so placed it that if it should be moved it would ring the bell - on the 30th of March, about half-past seven o'clock in the morning the bell rang - I was not down stairs at the time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-221-person2083">
                  GEORGE 
                  PATRICK
               <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2083" type="surname" value="PATRICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2083" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-221-person2083" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Richardson, and was in the shop when the bell rang. I was aware of the bell, and then looked towards the window, and saw that some one had pushed the box aside. I saw the prisoner's hand in pulling out the telescope, I then went and took him about thirty yards from the window - he had it partly out, and I saw him with it. The telescope was at one side of the box, and it was removed about six inches from the place it was first in.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. Q. There was a compass-box removed to make room for a persons hand - A. Yes; the telescope was removed six inches towards the hole. I saw the prisoner's face, and am quite sure that he was the lad that had his hand through the window - there were two other lads with him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw two lads looking into a window, and after they were gone, two young men came and immediately charged me with taking the telescope. They took me to the shop, and he said</p>
               <p>"I have caught you at last."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-221-verdict1283" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200412-221-verdict1283" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>
